Did you know that?

26:38.229 --> 26:40.229
No.

26:47.606 --> 26:51.542
-Pauline wins! Mom cheated.
-I did not.

26:51.643 --> 26:53.535
You didn't touch the wall, Margot.

26:53.545 --> 26:56.708
It doesn't matter. Lost anyway.

26:56.815 --> 26:58.815
It was close.

27:01.519 --> 27:04.324
Maisy, aren't you going swimming?

27:46.564 --> 27:48.564
Claude!

27:51.503 --> 27:53.503
Are you okay?

27:53.705 --> 27:55.705
I got him!

28:00.712 --> 28:02.712
It's okay, baby.

28:12.357 --> 28:16.777
-I'm sorry I laughed about the tree.
-Now we're even.

28:20.632 --> 28:23.625
-You've got a problem.
-What do you mean?

28:23.635 --> 28:24.826
I don't like the girl,

28:24.836 --> 28:26.961
and I don't like the way
Malcolm looks at her.

28:26.971 --> 28:28.196
Come on, it's sexy.

28:28.206 --> 28:30.732
No, you didn't see it.
I saw it. You've got a problem.

28:30.742 --> 28:32.742
I'm not worried.

28:33.712 --> 28:36.347
Maybe teach Claude how to swim.

28:36.381 --> 28:39.611
He won't want to do it. It's too late.

28:40.685 --> 28:44.000
-Are you supposed to be doing that?
-No.

28:45.423 --> 28:48.950
I liked your last story. Was it Harper's?
The one about Mom.

28:48.960 --> 28:51.935
I was very... I liked it very much.

28:52.597 --> 28:56.507
-It wasn't really about Mom.
-I thought it was.

28:56.634 --> 28:59.527
Anyway. Why don't you want
Claude to know how to swim?

28:59.537 --> 29:02.864
I didn't say I didn't want him to.
Why do you care?

29:02.874 --> 29:04.332
It's not in his life. We're New Yorkers.

29:04.342 --> 29:07.001
