happened to him?

42:50.701 --> 42:54.361
Why would you think that's
something I would do? That's awful.

42:54.371 --> 43:00.406
I didn't mean on purpose. I just meant
maybe in case you knew something.

43:02.112 --> 43:05.878
-Sorry. I'm here.
-I didn't see you.

43:05.983 --> 43:07.341
I'm just writing my vows.

43:07.351 --> 43:10.244
Trying to do something appropriate,
but also funny.

43:10.254 --> 43:13.484
Not jokey, more character-based humor.

43:14.224 --> 43:16.264
You having an okay time?

43:16.327 --> 43:19.132
Yeah, besides Wizard getting out.

43:19.163 --> 43:21.631
Yeah. We'll find him.

43:22.566 --> 43:23.857
Or else, I don't know.

43:23.867 --> 43:25.092
-We won't.
-Right.

43:25.102 --> 43:27.822
Or else, he's dead or something.

43:28.105 --> 43:31.845
-It means a lot to Paul that you came.
-Yeah.

43:37.381 --> 43:40.975
That is the same toaster
we had here as kids.

43:40.985 --> 43:42.985
Paul is so weird.

43:43.821 --> 43:46.213
I hear you've heard the news.

43:46.223 --> 43:48.987
Yeah. Congratulations.

43:49.093 --> 43:54.533
Pretty cool. Hard to fully take in.
It's still a little abstract.

43:54.698 --> 43:56.290
I haven't had that thing yet
where you realize

43:56.300 --> 44:00.890
that you're not the most important
person in the world.

44:01.739 --> 44:04.374
I'm anxious for that to happen.

44:04.842 --> 44:10.237
I guess I have to thank you.
I wouldn't know yet if you hadn't arrived.

44:10.247 --> 44:11.572
You're welcome.

44:11.582 --> 44:15.909
Of course I can't help but worry I'll pass
not-so-great genes on to the kid.

44:15.919 --> 44:18.278
I mean, in my family
there's a lot of hand washing, but...

44:18.288 --> 44:21.415
I don't have it, but my brother does.

44:21.425 --> 44:24.518
-Are you working on anything now?
-Besides the thing with Dick?

44:24.528 --> 44:26.453
Oh, right. Yeah.

44:26.463 --> 44:27.621
How about you?

44:27.631 --> 44:33.394
-I'm working on some abstract...
-No one fills the ice cube trays here.

44:33.404 --> 44:35.729
-Sorry, what were you saying?
-No. It's okay.

44:35.739 --> 44:39.233
-No, what were you saying?
-It really... Nothing.

44:39.243 --> 44:41.769
-Okay.
-I was saying I'm working on some

44:41.779 --> 44:44.772
abstractions in acrylic paint,
but it's not...

44:44.782 --> 44:46.674
I'm not getting paid or anything.

44:46.684 --> 44:49.610
I don't know.
I hate that question, "What do you do?"

44:49.620 --> 44:52.350
-You asked me.
-I know, but...

44:56.093 --> 44:57.985
I think we shouldn't mention the tree.

44:57.995 --> 45:00.254
We should let them know there'll be
people and music on Saturday,

45:00.264 --> 45:01.622
and it'll be louder than usual.

45:01.632 --> 45:03.424
Yeah, and they can come over
for a glass of champagne,

45:03.434 --> 45:05.659
but you tell them.
I think they respond to you better.

45:05.669 --> 45:07.594
Well, I am ultimately one of them.

45:07.604 --> 45:09.296
You shouldn't have made me
shave the 'stache.

45:09.306 --> 45:10.397
Yeah, right.

45:10.407 --> 45:14.735
Hey. Ingrid is asking if I was ever gay.
Do you know what that's about?

45:14.745 --> 45:16.745
No.

45:22.186 --> 45:25.986
Hi. I'm Pauline. This is Malcolm.

45:26.090 --> 45:27.715
We met you before.
We're your neighbors.

45:27.725 --> 45:30.190
You gonna cut that tree down?

45:31.061 --> 45:32.653
Well, we grew up with that tree,

45:32.663 --> 45:34.722
and we're getting married
under it on Saturday.

45:34.732 --> 45:41.362
Its roots are growing into our property.
It's rotting. It's killing our plants.

45:43.073 --> 45:47.578
We had the tree doctor out
and he said it was healthy.

45:48.712 --> 45:50.904
-Would it hurt you to say anything?
-What do you want from me?

45:50.914 --> 45:52.206
You're making me do
the whole fucking thing.

45:52.216 --> 45:54.475
-You brought up the tree.
-He brought up the tree.

45:54.485 --> 45:57.745
I'm sorry. This was better thought
through back at the house.

45:57.755 --> 45:59.179
We were wondering
if you and your wife,

45:59.189 --> 46:02.549
I'm sorry, I forgot her name,
would like to come over for a glass...

46:02.559 --> 46:05.252
You should ask her.
She makes the plans.

46:05.262 --> 46:07.262
I'm gonna go in now.

46:10.667 --> 46:14.695
I feel like you didn't give me a chance
to say what I wanted to say.

46:14.705 --> 46:17.264
-I want to punch that guy in the nose.
-You've never hit anyone.

46:17.274 --> 46:18.632
-I have too!
-Who?

46:18.642 --> 46:20.334
Lots of people. You don't know them.

46:20.344 --> 46:22.302
They're not around
'cause I punched them.

46:22.312 --> 46:27.410
Don't laugh, Pauline. It's not funny.
I'll punch your sister!

46:27.420 --> 46:28.709
The threat is not out there.

46:28.719 --> 46:32.112
It's in our house.
It's sleeping in my studio.

46:32.122 --> 46:34.414
I mean, I wouldn't actually hit her.

46:34.424 --> 46:37.684
But I feel like doing it.
She's such a fucking idiot.

46:37.694 --> 46:39.453
She's not an idiot.
You might not like her.

46:39.463 --> 46:41.321
She is. She's an idiot! You're an idiot.

46:41.331 --> 46:43.524
-Jesus!
-You're both fucking morons.

46:43.534 --> 46:46.760
I am so fucking... I am trying so hard.

46:46.770 --> 46:48.395
You don't give me any credit!

46:48.405 --> 46:50.870
-What is wrong?
-I don't know.

46:51.275 --> 46:55.402
I have the emotional version
of whatever bad feng shui would be.

46:55.412 --> 46:58.305
I don't know. You tell me.
You understand this shit.

46:58.315 --> 47:02.075
-Did you drink your teas?
-Yeah, I drank my fucking teas.

47:02.085 --> 47:04.278
Really, I think when you look back
at this you're going to see

47:04.288 --> 47:07.714
I'm not acting like a crazy person.
That this is the right reaction.

47:07.724 --> 47:11.889
In proportion with what's going on,
this is right.

47:19.937 --> 47:21.937
Let's make love.

47:31.281 --> 47:33.613
-Jim.
-Hey.

47:34.518 --> 47:36.518
How are you?

47:37.588 --> 47:39.584
-Dad!
-Claude!

47:39.594 --> 47:41.590
Hey.

47:41.725 --> 47:42.983
It was a difficult decision,

47:42.993 --> 47:45.752
because Claude has so many friends
in school now.

47:45.762 --> 47:49.656
But it's expensive, and Bronx Science
is a great public school.

47:49.666 --> 47:51.391
I didn't get into Stuyvesant.

47:51.401 --> 47:55.141
-He's not a good test taker.
-I went to Stuy.

47:55.272 --> 47:57.272
-Really?
-Really.

47:57.374 --> 48:00.400
I'd rather stay at Packer,
but it's so expensive.

48:00.410 --> 48:03.737
Josh is a great test taker,
but Claude thinks more abstractly.

48:03.747 --> 48:07.062
-He's more creative. Right?
-I guess so.

48:07.384 --> 48:11.144
I saw the one-armed man,
who really has two arms, at the bodega.

48:11.154 --> 48:13.580
Really?
Did you give him confusing change?

48:13.590 --> 48:19.019
I did. I tripped him up with some nickels
and a Canadian quarter.

48:19.029 --> 48:23.789
You know what I tried the other day?
Sitting down to pee.

48:23.934 --> 48:25.974
Have you done this, Jim?

48:26.503 --> 48:28.503
No.

48:29.473 --> 48:30.797
I haven't.

48:30.807 --> 48:32.866
It was a joke, really.
I was gonna call in Pauline

48:32.876 --> 48:34.668
and say, "Guess what I'm doing here?"

48:34.678 --> 48:36.470
Sorry I didn't get to have
that experience.

48:36.480 --> 48:38.272
I was just thinking, you know,

48:38.282 --> 48:41.108
my dad used to say,
"Why stand when you can sit?"

48:41.118 --> 48:43.577
And this is a really good example
of that.

48:43.587 --> 48:45.946
I mean, it took me a long time to try,
'cause I was embarrassed.

48:45.956 --> 48:47.314
But you guys do it all the time.

48:47.324 --> 48:50.817
I never sit in a public place.
I always squat and hover.

48:50.827 --> 48:54.154
Anyway, I recommend it.
At least to try it.

48:54.164 --> 48:55.923
Jim, I'm sorry about the room.

48:55.933 --> 48:59.860
It's usually Malcolm's storage room.
So, it's kind of makeshift right now.

48:59.870 --> 49:01.870
It's fine.

49:02.839 --> 49:04.839
Margot, open your gift.

49:05.642 --> 49:08.635
I get self-conscious opening presents
in front of people.

49:08.645 --> 49:09.136
I get self-conscious opening presents
in front of people.

49:09.146 --> 49:15.011
-Anyway, this weekend is about Pauline.
-Pooh, Margot. Go on, open it.

49:26.697 --> 49:28.737
Get on with it. Come on.

49:35.906 --> 49:37.331
Those look warm.

49:37.341 --> 49:42.781
I remember last year in Vermont
you said your feet were freezing.

49:44.147 --> 49:46.147
Thank you.

49:47.117 --> 49:49.117
You're welcome.

49:51.154 --> 49:53.194
I already have slippers.

49:53.290 --> 49:56.520
That's okay. Two sets are fine, right?

49:58.261 --> 50:01.888
It makes me sad to get
a present I already have.

50:01.898 --> 50:05.891
-Why?
-Makes me feel like you don't know me.

50:10.507 --> 50:11.665
What's wrong with your ear?

50:11.675 --> 50:14.868
I asked you not to come
and you did it anyway, so blithely.

50:14.878 --> 50:17.838
We need time alone to sort this out.
You can't just run away.

50:17.848 --> 50:19.940
Okay, we're here.
I'm giving you this time.

50:19.950 --> 50:21.950
Well...

50:21.985 --> 50:25.555
Now you're putting
too much pressure on me.

50:29.893 --> 50:31.518
What is that?

50:31.528 --> 50:34.292
Keep driving. Jim, Jim. No!

50:34.398 --> 50:36.398
-I'm just seeing.
-No.

50:39.102 --> 50:41.102
Stay right there.

50:45.208 --> 50:47.574
Please help me.

50:47.677 --> 50:51.374
-Please. He got hit by a car.
-Jim.

50:52.349 --> 50:54.241
Jim.

50:54.251 --> 50:58.045
-Careful. He might bite you.
-I got him. I got him.

50:58.055 --> 51:00.055
Hurry, he's dying!

51:00.824 --> 51:02.349
He didn't do anything.

51:02.359 --> 51:05.452
Roger's an innocent.
He's an innocent creature.

51:05.462 --> 51:06.853
-Oh, God.
-Margot.

51:06.863 --> 51:08.956
I can't stand her.

51:16.807 --> 51:18.765
You paid, didn't you?

51:18.775 --> 51:23.103
She didn't have her purse with her.
It wasn't so expensive.

51:23.113 --> 51:24.604
Roger's gonna live.

51:24.614 --> 51:30.139
I don't give a fuck about Roger,
and that makes me feel like shit.

51:30.754 --> 51:33.049
You make me feel like shit.

51:34.224 --> 51:36.116
-I wouldn't have stopped.
-Of course you would have.

51:36.126 --> 51:38.126
No, I wouldn't have.

51:38.829 --> 51:43.249
-I hate myself when I'm with you.
-Margot, I'm not...

51:46.536 --> 51:48.462
I can't talk to you
when you're this fucked up.

51:48.472 --> 51:52.933
You're just like Claude in that way.
You make me feel guilty.

51:52.943 --> 51:56.003
Sometimes, I find you so despicable.

52:19.503 --> 52:21.503
What's wrong?

52:24.107 --> 52:26.107
I don't know.

52:28.545 --> 52:34.325
Before you gave me your sweater,
I don't think I realized I was cold.

52:38.455 --> 52:40.582
Take me home and go away.

52:42.692 --> 52:47.521
If it were someone else,
I'd understand it. I'd feel sympathy even.

52:47.531 --> 52:52.291
But since it's me,
I just feel bad and horribly critical.

52:52.736 --> 52:54.594
I haven't been able to tell Claude
what's happening,

52:54.604 --> 52:56.984
and I have to. I'm going to.

52:57.207 --> 53:00.367
How can I be all these people?
How can I be married to Jim

53:00.377 --> 53:03.336
and fuck Dick and want them both,
and then neither of them?

53:03.346 --> 53:07.941
I know. We're at that age where
we're becoming invisible to men.

53:07.951 --> 53:11.678
If a guy wants to fuck us,
that's very tempting.

53:11.688 --> 53:12.846
What are you saying?

53:12.856 --> 53:16.082
I'm saying if you get your sense of self
from being fuckable

53:16.092 --> 53:19.152
and that starts to wane, it's very hard.

53:19.162 --> 53:22.923
I almost had an affair, too.
But you don't have to do it.

53:22.933 --> 53:27.233
You can, I don't know,
get a manicure or something.

53:29.606 --> 53:33.233
You know, I tell people
you're my closest friend.

53:33.243 --> 53:36.007
-I really miss you.
-Me, too.

53:36.112 --> 53:38.338
But I can't help feeling
that you really came to my wedding

53:38.348 --> 53:41.274
'cause I live a mile away
from the guy you're fucking.

53:41.284 --> 53:44.477
Come on, Pauline,
you make it sound like I'm using you.

53:44.487 --> 53:46.487
Yeah.

53:47.357 --> 53:49.357
You've got a...

53:50.060 --> 53:52.270
-Did I get it?
-I think so.

53:53.897 --> 53:56.756
Pauline, what are you doing
getting married to this guy?

53:56.766 --> 53:59.960
He's not good enough for you.
He's so coarse.

53:59.970 --> 54:03.363
He's like guys we rejected
when we were 1 6.

54:03.373 --> 54:06.700
You know,
don't make a mistake like this.

54:06.710 --> 54:08.668
I'm sorry. Maybe I have no right to say it.

54:08.678 --> 54:13.098
But you know I'm truthful,
so would you rather I lie?

54:14.584 --> 54:16.209
Who should I be with then?

54:16.219 --> 54:19.449
I don't know.
Someone who's your equal.

54:20.223 --> 54:23.783
You're so smart. You're brilliant.
You're funny.

54:23.793 --> 54:27.053
You're incredibly hilarious.
Paul, you're a great teacher.

54:27.063 --> 54:30.633
You're open to things.
You're so beautiful.

54:31.034 --> 54:33.764
Hey! Hey, you! You pick that up.

54:33.870 --> 54:36.396
I will call the police.
This is our property.

54:36.406 --> 54:38.406
Creeps.

54:54.157 --> 54:55.849
Wizard!

54:55.859 --> 54:58.852
-What happened to your dad?
-He went to Vermont.

54:58.862 --> 55:00.420
He didn't want to come to the wedding?

55:00.430 --> 55:04.170
I don't think he could. I think he couldn't.

55:04.501 --> 55:07.436
-You want to see me dance?
-Okay.

55:21.685 --> 55:23.685
Wizard.

55:24.321 --> 55:26.321
You're not watching.

55:33.296 --> 55:36.526
-Where you going?
-We have to get home.

55:40.070 --> 55:43.330
-Is that your girlfriend?
-No, she's my cousin.

55:43.340 --> 55:46.173
-You a fruity?
-No.

55:46.276 --> 55:48.836
-You a fruity?
-No.

55:54.984 --> 55:56.042
He's a Vogler.

55:56.052 --> 55:59.079
-Come on. He's just a stupid boy.
-Wait. I have a rock in my shoe.

55:59.089 --> 56:00.947
Come on, Ingrid!

56:00.957 --> 56:02.957
Liar!

56:04.127 --> 56:06.127
Ingrid, get him off me!

56:07.564 --> 56:10.156
You're fucking gay. You're fucking gay.

56:10.166 --> 56:12.166
No.

56:22.011 --> 56:24.011
Hangman's ass.

56:33.423 --> 56:35.973
-Don't run so fast.
-He bit me.

56:36.059 --> 56:38.425
-Who bit you?
-A Vogler.

56:38.528 --> 56:40.528
Let me see.

56:43.366 --> 56:45.291
All right. That's it. I'm calling the police.

56:45.301 --> 56:48.528
Don't! It'll get worse.
Why did you say anything to them?

56:48.538 --> 56:50.797
What are you talking about?
This isn't my fault.

56:50.807 --> 56:54.000
That boy bit me 'cause you couldn't
keep your fat mouth shut.

56:54.010 --> 56:56.002
Claude, you're being a jerk.

56:56.012 --> 56:59.752
You shit in your shoes
and then you fuck 'em!

57:00.945 --> 57:04.090
She wrote a story about Lenny and me.

57:05.283 --> 57:07.283
Yeah. It's in here.

57:08.219 --> 57:10.711
I mean, we were talking
almost every day at this point,

57:10.721 --> 57:12.280
and there was no warning.

57:12.290 --> 57:16.450
I mean, maybe a couple of remarks
that she'd used some things of ours.

57:16.460 --> 57:19.020
And then The New Yorker comes,
we have a subscription,

57:19.030 --> 57:21.026
and there's the story.

57:21.036 --> 57:25.793
And it's things we said and did.
Stuff I told her in confidence.

57:25.803 --> 57:28.062
I think it helped end our marriage.

57:28.072 --> 57:31.803
I read it and I thought, "She hates me."

57:31.909 --> 57:33.909
She doesn't hate you.

57:34.445 --> 57:36.445
You think?

57:37.181 --> 57:40.374
Margot tried to murder me
when we were girls.

57:40.384 --> 57:42.910
She put me on a baking sheet,
sprinkled me with paprika,

57:42.920 --> 57:44.920
and put me in the oven.

57:49.360 --> 57:51.360
Jim was here.

57:51.762 --> 57:53.762
Is Jim still writing?

57:55.032 --> 57:58.347
I told him to go to Vermont without me.

57:58.803 --> 58:03.223
I'd like to see him tell a linear story
for a change.

58:03.541 --> 58:05.700
Jim never wanted to make it easy
for the reader, did he?

58:05.710 --> 58:10.215
The nicest man I ever met,
but he can't play the game.

58:10.881 --> 58:15.046
I'm not gonna be joining him.
I'm gonna stay here.

58:15.419 --> 58:17.419
We'll see.

58:18.356 --> 58:20.356
All right?

58:21.192 --> 58:23.192
Okay?

58:24.061 --> 58:26.441
I didn't ask you to do that.

58:29.967 --> 58:32.262
That guy is pointing at us.

58:33.104 --> 58:37.331
I'm very interested in your story
"Middle Children."

58:37.341 --> 58:40.538
The father is a loathsome character,

58:40.644 --> 58:44.299
yet we also feel
a strange sympathy for him.

58:45.850 --> 58:51.812
Well, I was really interested in exploring
a father/daughter relationship.

58:51.822 --> 58:57.988
While he clings to her,
desperately, he suffocates her really.

58:58.429 --> 59:04.425
He also silently resents
the responsibility of parenthood.

59:06.070 --> 59:09.663
There's this sexualized
push-pull with Daphne,

59:09.673 --> 59:13.769
-which I find...
-He craves isolation.

59:14.912 --> 59:17.104
I always saw him as someone who

59:17.114 --> 59:20.914
so over-identifies with
everyone around him

59:22.086 --> 59:25.920
that he begins to lose
all sense of himself.

59:26.590 --> 59:28.916
But you make his only recourse
to abandon his family,

59:28.926 --> 59:33.601
-including his beloved daughter.
-Yes, yes, that's true.

59:34.432 --> 59:38.392
I write historical fiction,
so I don't have to answer to this,

59:38.402 --> 59:42.329
but I wonder, for someone
who writes so nakedly about family,

59:42.339 --> 59:45.740
how autobiographical is this portrait?

59:47.711 --> 59:49.937
My father was a loving person.

59:49.947 --> 59:53.107
He had his days, of course,
but he was devoted to us as children.

59:53.117 --> 59:57.707
I would never have written this portrait,
were it true.

59:58.322 --> 01:00:04.527
But I'm interested in how the father
could be, in fact, a portrait of you.

01:00:08.499 --> 01:00:10.499
I don't...

01:00:11.669 --> 01:00:14.219
Why do you assume that it's...

01:00:15.072 --> 01:00:18.132
That, I mean, we all take from life.

01:00:22.179 --> 01:00:25.005
I had to have our refrigerator repaired
the other day

01:00:25.015 --> 01:00:27.575
at our apartment in Manhattan,

01:00:27.685 --> 01:00:32.088
and I was alone with this guy.

01:00:32.189 --> 01:00:33.981
I think he was Puerto Rican.

01:00:33.991 --> 01:00:37.483
He was sent over by Whirlpool,

01:00:37.595 --> 01:00:41.463
who I think it is, makes our fridge.

01:00:44.602 --> 01:00:47.595
Although he did say that he worked for
an independent organization,

01:00:47.605 --> 01:00:49.985
that Whirlpool subcontracts.

01:00:50.708 --> 01:00:52.748
I think he was retarded.

01:00:55.779 --> 01:00:57.779
There was...

01:00:58.382 --> 01:01:03.183
There was an anger in him,
and suddenly,

01:01:04.455 --> 01:01:07.600
suddenly I became afraid for my life.

01:01:10.394 --> 01:01:14.922
I called Jim at NYU, and I...

01:01:15.099 --> 01:01:17.224
I asked him to come home.

01:01:22.606 --> 01:01:26.431
I think it was Frigidaire
who made our fridge.

01:01:29.847 --> 01:01:34.437
I'm gonna need...
I'm gonna need to take a moment here.

01:01:44.428 --> 01:01:46.428
You're an asshole.

01:02:01.478 --> 01:02:04.939
-I need to be alone right now, okay?
-What's wrong?

01:02:04.949 --> 01:02:09.181
I don't know.
I'll tell you sometime. Go on.

01:02:09.653 --> 01:02:11.011
